UDP-N-acetylglucosamine 1-carboxyvinyltransferase 1 (EC 2.5.1.7)
(Enoylpyruvate transferase 1) (UDP-N-acetylglucosamine enolpyruvyl
transferase 1) (EPT 1).
"Comparative genomics of Listeria species.";
-!- FUNCTION: Cell wall formation. Adds enolpyruvyl to UDP-N-
    acetylglucosamine (By similarity).
-!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: Phosphoenolpyruvate + UDP-N-acetyl-D-
    glucosamine = phosphate + UDP-N-acetyl-3-O-(1-carboxyvinyl)-D-
    glucosamine.
-!- PATHWAY: Glycan biosynthesis; peptidoglycan biosynthesis.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Cytoplasm (Probable).
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the EPSP synthase family. MurA subfamily.
